<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Saprobic on decaying branches of an unidentified plant. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Stromata</emphasis>
immersed in bark, aggregated, irregular in shape, widely effused, flat, margin diffuse, surface dark brown to black, with punctiform ostioles scattered at surface, with tissues soft, white between perithecia. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Entostroma</emphasis>
dark with embedded perithecia in one layer. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Perithecium</emphasis>
semi-immersed in stroma, globose to subglobose, glabrous, with cylindrical neck, brevicollous or longicollous 283.5-343.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high, 207-290 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
broad (av. = 315.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
248.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 10), ovoid, obovoid to oblong, monostichous, aterrimus. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ostiole</emphasis>
opening separately, papillate or apapillate, central. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peridium</emphasis>
30-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
thick, dark brown to hyaline with 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">textura angularis</emphasis>
cell layers. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asci</emphasis>
90.5-160.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.0-15.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(av. = 129.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
n = 30) 8-spored clavate, unitunicate, with rounded apex, apical rings inamyloid. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascospores</emphasis>
11-18.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(av. = 14.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 30), irregularly arranged, allantoid, slightly curved, brown to dark brown, smooth, aseptate, usually with oil droplets. Asexual morph: undetermined.
</paragraph>
